Dramatic evidence from the investigating officer emerged in the murder case of Karabo Mokoena in court today.A deal was struck which allowed the reporting from the bail application of her boyfriend Sandile Mantsoe in the Johannesburg Magistrate s Court, but media are not allowed to name the witnesses.The investigating officer, with 31 years of investigating cases of abuse and violence against women and children, gave this testimony.The officer explained that Mantsoe needed to kill Mokoena because he needed to destroy a jinks which had followed him after the couple broke up.The officer said there is no evidence that she was suicidal, but that there was evidence he had abused her prior to her murder.Mantsoe had made an admission when he was arrested for her kidnapping that he burnt her so police wouldn t link him to death of the girl.He had told the police he had to kill Mokoena because when he met her, and they fell in love, she introduced him to some traditional ritual.Both cut their bodies, the officer said. Both marked their bodies with a tattoo in shape of a cross to ensure there&#8217;s a lasting bond between them.This would also enable his business to thrive.The reason for his business not doing well was because of a jinx after he broke up with her, he could only break the jinx by killing her.He believed that since both their blood were mixed and they still had a bond, he had to cut the bond and kill her for the success of his business, the officer told the court. Clear that he would have to kill her in order to stop the spiritual bond, he said in his affidavit.Mantsoe was aware of security cameras and used trolley bin to move her body out of the apartment on the fourth floor.He bought petrol and tyre with pool acid too.The officer believed there was a strong probability that Mantsoe will interfere with the investigation.He had burnt the body beyond recognition so that there is no trace of evidence. The accused has removed deceased clothes from the apartment and he gave the clothes to his family.The couple were in a relationship from October last year, broke up in April.She was admitted to hospital after he beat up.On April 27 before midnight picked her up from Diepkloof. She was seen entering the apartment, that was last time that decreased was seen alive.He comes out alone to go for a meeting with a client. Footage him alone, emerging from their Sandton Skye flat in Sandton.A body of an unknown female discovered, burned beyond recognition and identified through DNA as Mokoena.Family and friends worried about her disappearance. They tried calling, but no answer. They asked the accused her whereabouts and he denied, saying he last saw her in beginning of April.Information was that decreased last seen at Sandton Skye. May 10, 2017, she was reported as missing, family accompanied by police approached him and he continued to say he didn&#8217;t know her whereabouts even after they watched security footage showing both of them together in April.He was arrested then for kidnapping because they couldn&#8217;t determine if she was still alive. Applicant made an admission before Commissioner of Oaths that he took her to an open veld in Bramley, poured swimming pool acid over her and burned body.When he took them to the place where he set her alight.It was not clear if she was alive or not when he burnt.Post-mortem report still pending.The officer said the accused should not be granted bail as it came to his attention that he was blaming on of the witnesses and said the only reason he was arrested is that the witness told police about the burnt body.&#8211; Canny Maphanga